    dc:date "2018" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Amolops (Anura: Ranidae) from southwestern Guangdong, China" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1245420>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1245422>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1245418> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1245420>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Morphological features of the adult male holotype SYS a004705 of Amolops yunkaiensis sp. nov. in life. (A) dorsolateral view; (B) ventral view; (C) left hand; (D) left foot; (E) nuptial pad and nuptial spines; (F) sparse translucent tubercles on the lower jaw and forechest." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1245420/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1245422>
    dc:description "FIGURE4. Comparisons of morphologicalcharacteristics among Amolops yunkaiensis sp. nov., A.torrentis and species in the A. rickettispecies group.(A) Amolopsyunkaiensis sp.nov.; (B) A.torrentis; (C)A.albispinus; (D) A.ricketti; (E) A.wuyiensis. (1) dorsolateralview; (2) close-up of the head; (3) ventral view of the hand; (4) ventral view of the leg." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1245422/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1245418>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Bayesian inference and maximum-likelihood phylogenies. Numbers above branches indicate Bayesian posterior probabilities (BPP> 0.95 retained, “*” signifies “1.00”) and numbers below branches are bootstrap support for maximum likelihood (1000 replicates) analysis (BS> 70 retained, “*” signifies “100”)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1245418/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

